Digital security company Irdeto has acquired anti-piracy firm Denuvo. The companies will join forces to combat video game piracy across desktop, mobile, console, and VR platforms. The partnership is aimed at expanding the market for Denuvo’s anti-piracy services. The company will continue to operate normally while retaining its staff, while its product offering will be bolstered by Irdeto’s Cloakware technology. Current Denuvo customers include Electronic Arts, UbiSoft, Warner Bros, and Lionsgate Entertainment. Irdeto is a subsidiary of Naspers.